OL,3,CWhy is this Budget so important for
OL,4,Cthe UK economy?
OL,6,FFirms were affected by the increase in
OL,7,Fthe national minimum wage, higher
OL,8,FNational Insurance Contributions
OL,9,F(NICs), reduced business rates
OL,10,Fdiscounts and other taxes, such as a
OL,11,Fnew packaging tax.
OL,13,FThe Bank of England highlighted that
OL,14,Fthe increase in NICs and the minimum
OL,15,Fwage partly contributed to higher food
OL,16,Fprice inflation earlier this year as
OL,17,Fimpacted firms passed some of this on
OL,18,Fto their customers.
