OL,3,CWhy is this Budget so important for
OL,4,Cthe UK economy?
OL,6,FRuth Gregory at Capital Economics
OL,7,Fsaid: "The risk is that the fourth
OL,8,Fquarter isn't a golden one for
OL,9,Fretailers and that higher taxes in the
OL,10,FBudget restrain retail spending over
OL,11,Fthe crucial festive period and going
OL,12,Finto next year."
OL,14,F` Why has there been focus on the
OL,15,FGovernment's 'fiscal hole' and what
OL,16,Fdoes this mean?
OL,18,FThe so-called "fiscal hole" is the gap
OL,19,Fbetween the Government's projected
OL,20,Fspending and its projected revenues,
OL,21,Ftypically through taxes or borrowing.
