OL,3,CWhy is this Budget so important for
OL,4,Cthe UK economy?
OL,6,FThis is particularly important for the
OL,7,FGovernment as it seeks to meet the
OL,8,Ffiscal rule that it must balance
OL,9,Fspending and revenues over the next
OL,10,Ffive years.
OL,12,FEconomists have predicted that a
OL,13,Fsignificant "fiscal hole" has grown
OL,14,Fsince the last spending review, with
OL,15,Fspending reductions lower than
OL,16,Fexpected because of failures to pass
OL,17,Fwelfare cuts, increased borrowing
OL,18,Fcosts and expected readjustment to
OL,19,Fproductivity forecasts.
